For a sec-butyl group, a larger alkyl side chain, we could estimate a reduction of around -30°C due to the increase in steric bulk which disrupts crystalline packing. Therefore, the combined effect of the two functional groups would reduce the initial melting point of barbituric acid by around -50°C.
